
1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In 1942, World War II was at its peak.

2
00:00:03,001 --> 00:00:06,500
India was dragged into it without consent.

3
00:00:06,501 --> 00:00:09,000
Mahatma Gandhi launched the Quit India Movement.

4
00:00:09,001 --> 00:00:12,000
His call was bold: "Do or Die."

5
00:00:12,001 --> 00:00:15,000
The movement spread across the nation like wildfire.

6
00:00:15,001 --> 00:00:18,000
Protests erupted, people demanded independence.

7
00:00:18,001 --> 00:00:21,000
British police cracked down harshly.

8
00:00:21,001 --> 00:00:23,500
Gandhi and other leaders were jailed.

9
00:00:23,501 --> 00:00:26,500
Still, underground activities kept the fire alive.

10
00:00:26,501 --> 00:00:30,000
The Quit India Movement shook the foundations of colonial rule.

11
00:00:30,001 --> 00:00:33,000
The road to freedom was now irreversible.

